<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Which would most likely shift the money demand curve to the left?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">An increase in real GDP</option>
            <option letter="b">An increase in the price level</option>
            <option letter="c">The introduction of widespread credit card use</option>
            <option letter="d">A decrease in financial technology</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>The introduction of widespread credit card use would shift the money demand curve left because people need to hold less money for transactions. When new financial technologies make it easier to make purchases without cash, the demand for money decreases at every interest rate.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
